Package com.zanderwohl.chunks.World

Class Volume

java.lang.Object
com.zanderwohl.chunks.Delta.Delta
com.zanderwohl.chunks.World.Volume
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Volume
extends Delta
implements java.io.Serializable
A unit of blocks in three dimensions that has a height, width and depth. Is stored as a single file, and is given a generator in order to generate and populate its own contents when called to do so
See Also:

  • Method Details

    • load

      public static Volume load​(java.lang.String location) throws java.io.IOException
      Load data into this Volume from a file. Currently supports only blocks with no specific data, as well as an internal marker of location.
      Parameters:
      location - The name of the file, including the extension.
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - If the file specified is not found, or perhaps locked by another process.

      Parameters:
      saveName - The name to save the Volume under.

    • getMaxHeight

      public int getMaxHeight​(int x, int z)
      Get the maximum y-value at a particular location. The maximum is the highest y-value in the Volume that does not have air.
      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate.
      z - The z-coordinate.
      Returns:
      The maximum height in this column.

    • hasMaxHeight

      public boolean hasMaxHeight​(int x, int z)
      Get whether the given column has a maximum; in other words, if it is not empty.
      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate.
      z - The z-coordinate.
      Returns:
      True if there is a maximum, false otherwise.

    • getMaxBlock

      public int getMaxBlock​(int x, int z)
      Get the block type id in at the highest position in the particular column. The block type id is specified by the Block Library. It may change per-instance, per-run.
      Parameters:
      x - The x-coordinate.
      z - The z-coordinate.
      Returns:
      The block type id at the maximum filled height in the specified column.
